@Olinea: I've now made seven posts since confirmation, you've made eleven. chamber has made fifteen.<br>
<br>
And activity levels and # of posts are not related. You can spam one-liners all you want, it doesn't mean you're very active in the game. All it does is confuse the town. Cyberbob summed it up the best. This game is the farthest thing from coherent.<br>
<br>
@all: No more joking/sarcasm/rhetoric stuff. It only gets confusing in the end.

@el simo: So you were just bandwagoning to encourage discussion?<br>
<br>
@chamber: I seriously doubt that.

@Olinea, Pie: This is the same thing Pie did in GHM1, if I remember correctly. I'm not saying he's scum here, but everyone went along with what he said in GHM1, and the town lost because of it (his mafia team did too, but that's not the point <img class="smilies" src="./images/smilies/icon_biggrin.gif" width="15" height="15" alt=":D" title="Very Happy">) . Link for those who weren't in the game: <a href="http://www.scorehero.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=100099&amp;start=0" class="postlink"></a><a href="http://www.scorehero.com/forum/viewtopic.php?t=100099&amp;start=0" class="postlink">http://www.scorehero.com/forum/viewtopi ... 99&amp;start=0</a><br>
<br>
Point is, I just don't want people to go necessarily go along with these groups Pie has made solely because he's...made them. Those are his (valid) opinions, but people looking at these groups should take other things into account, and not take them to heart so quickly (I don't know if people have yet).

Olinea:  Do you have any scumreads?  I've seen you defending all the top lynch candidates, but not calling anyone scum.  Do you still think el simo is scum?  (I think that's where your vote is)<br>
<br>
I feel like you did this last game and you weren't town then. &gt;_&gt;

Oh, and I never said whOever posts the least is the scummiest. Misrep +1<br>
<br>
El simo says that's a scum-tell. I learn fast. &gt;_&gt;

@el simo: It's because I'm a Jester. <br>
<br>
@Pie: I don't really care about townie points.

@Pie: More important things have come up than defending stupid arguments in a mafia game. They're SO stupid, I don't even remember what they are. So, no. I probably won't do it anymore. Lynch me if you wish.<br>
<br>
@Fugitive: I am agreeing with Furcolow's feelings in his post. It's like, who even cares anymore.

@Fugitive: You want to know why I want to be lynched? I guess I want to show everyone that people make up "scum tells," because I'm not scum. You know that "whiny scum meta" you talk about? That doesn't even apply here, anyway. When I'm scum, I don't even play the game at all. I lurk for days or weeks at a time. I threaten replacement. I'm just pissed off in this game, mostly at people like el simo and Umbrage that have some sort of elitist attitude; I think you guys deserve to learn a little about the game and rethink everything you think you know. Lynch me, see I'm a Vanilla Townie (yes, that's my claim. inb4 scum claim), feel stupid. <br>
<br>
If I'm lynched, DO NOT let anyone say anything along the lines of, "But he was acting so scummy! I was sure he was scum!" I'm sure many people will do this, and if you REALLY look at my posts, you'll see they weren't really so scummy after all.

@Fugitive: I know it's neither productive nor mature. When people tell me to "stop fucking crying" and to "stop being a lazy bum," I don't react positively. <br>
<br>
@el simo: I'm not scummy, first off. People like you make me 1) not want to play the game and 2) not want to take the game seriously, because I can't have fun when people like you are in games I play in.

@Pie: &gt;____&gt; I mentioned el simo because he was one of the ones who was getting most fed up with me. I was saying that if even he wants to hear what I have to say (I was already making a post at that point), maybe what I have to say is important after all. I'm not creating this post FOR el simo.<br>
<br>
If that all makes sense.

I am through Pie on the list in the OP. If I'm not done by 11, when I get off, do you want me to go ahead and post what I have? I'll probably be almost done by then.<br>
<br>
@DIDDIN: Umbrage is being replaced. I want an extension.

@Fugitive: It may seem like I took things out of context because I ISOed everyone instead of reading the thread straight through. Maybe I shouldn't have? Like I said, this was my first time ever doing anything like this. About Furcolow, I'm starting to think maybe he should have claimed Miller earlier. Why did he wait so long?<br>
<br>
I wasn't intentionally trying to misrepresent you. I thought you were saying I was playing my scum meta (whiny or something, which isn't my meta), and I guess I understand your views on agreeing with a lynch.

Okay, game started late so I can't formulate a great post, but I have a huge hunch either Z or Furc knew Thad was scum. Those two quick votes without a defense or claim (despite him flipping scum) do not sit well with me. I guarantee at least one is scum. Very possibly both. <br>
<br>
Other than that, I'd like BS to post more because she's completely flying under the radar and hasn't really added anything of value since replacing in. I did have a town read on chamber but that has all but disappeared into neutral since BS replaced in. <br>
<br>
I'll be analyzing Pie's play, votes, and votes on him tomorrow. <br>
